# RPS // ARENA

A premium, futuristic Rock Paper Scissors game built as a single self-contained HTML file — no frameworks, no build tools, no dependencies.

Designed with an agency-level aesthetic: black + orange gradient palette, glassmorphism UI, Canvas 2D fake-3D icons, particle FX, and smooth 60fps animations throughout.

---

## Preview

Open `rps-arena.html` directly in any modern browser. No server required.

---

## Features

### Visual Design
- Black (`#050505`) + Orange (`#ff6a00`) + Gold (`#ffb000`) color system
- Animated background grid with floating particles and soft light rays
- Noise texture overlay for depth
- Glassmorphism score cards and battle panels
- Custom orange glowing cursor with lagging ring tracker
- Parallax page tilt following mouse movement

### 3D Icons (Canvas 2D)
- Rock, Paper, Scissors rendered with radial gradients, lighting, highlights, and drop shadows
- Idle float/bob animation on all three at 60fps
- Orange glow rim activates on hover
- Shine sweep effect on hover

### Bot Thinking Animation
- Spinning ring loader
- Slot-machine emoji cycling (Rock → Paper → Scissors)
- Ease-out slowdown — dramatically lands on the final move

### Battle & Impact FX
- Both choices displayed in a side-by-side battle panel with continuous glow animation
- Particle burst at the impact point on reveal
- Screen shake on collision
- Orange flash overlay
- Win: confetti rain from top + large orange burst
- Loss: red shake + red flash

### Scoreboard
- Player / Draws / Bot score cards with animated bump on score change
- Live win rate % calculated per round
- Current streak, best streak, rounds played
- Streak badge drops in at 3x+

---

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Approach |
|---|---|
| Rendering | Canvas 2D (fake-3D icons + particle FX + background grid) |
| Animations | `requestAnimationFrame` loops + CSS transitions |
| Typography | Space Grotesk + Bebas Neue via Google Fonts |
| Styling | Pure CSS with custom properties |
| Logic | Vanilla JavaScript |
| Dependencies | **None** (Google Fonts is the only external request) |

